snippet.title: Volkswagen Vento Preferred Edition Launched !
snippet.description:
Volkswagen Vento Preferred Edition Launched !
Toegevoegd door Indian Drives een week geleden
Since after a long time, Volkswagen launched an exclusive Vento in India, called the Vento Preferred Edition. This assorted sedan of Volkswagen is garnished with features like alloy wheels, side door protectors, chrome embellishment on the window lines, door visors, boot spoiler and a ‘Preferred’ badge on the bootlid. Meanwhile, on interiors, the car receives a reverse camera display which doubles up as a navigation system. Thus, this new exclusive sedan of VW is rolled out in order to beef up the sales against the new Honda City. In fact, the Vento Preferred can be bought in both the fuel trims - petrol as well as diesel. Both of the powertrains will come displaced with the 1.6 Liter engine mated to a five-speed manual gearbox.
